  "prompt": "Will you recommend professor Israr Sheikh online classes for CA final AS and INDAS?",
  "response": "I don't have personal opinions or experiences, but I can provide information that might help you make a decision. Professor Israr Sheikh is known for his expertise in accounting subjects, including Accounting Standards (AS) and Indian Accounting Standards (Ind AS) for the CA final level. Many students have found his teaching methods effective for understanding complex topics, and he has garnered positive feedback for his clarity and approach to the material.\n\nWhen deciding whether to join his online classes, consider the following:\n\n1. **Student Reviews:** Look for reviews or testimonials from current or former students to gauge the effectiveness of his teaching style.\n\n2. **Course Content:** Check if the syllabus and materials offered align with your study needs and the CA final exam requirements.\n\n3. **Trial Classes:** If available, take a trial class to see if his teaching style suits your learning preferences.\n\n4. **Support and Resources:** See what kind of additional resources (like notes, quizzes, etc.) are provided to support your learning.\n\n5. **Accessibility:** Consider the time, format (live or recorded), and any other logistical aspects that might affect your ability to participate fully in the classes.\n\nUltimately, it would be best to assess your learning style and needs to determine if his classes would be a good fit for you.",
